      • reserveCriticalNodes

        public void reserveCriticalNodes()
        Certain input pins in a switch box can also serve as a bounce. We need to prevent the usage of the bounce if the pin will be need to route an input pin. This method reserves those wires by marking them used. They are later released as the routing for that particular net is starting.

      • markExistingRouteResourcesUsed

        public void markExistingRouteResourcesUsed()
        This router will preserve all existing routes (even partials) intact. This method will mark them as used to avoid route conflicts.

      • isNodeUsableStaticSource

        private boolean isNodeUsableStaticSource(RouteNode n,
                                         NetType type)
        This method handles queries during the static source routing process. It determines if the node in question can be used as a source for the current NetType.
        Parameters:
        n - The node in question
        type - The NetType to indicate what kind of static source we need (GND/VCC)
        Returns:
        True if the pin is a hard source or an unused LUT output that can be repurposed as a source

      • isThisOurStaticSource

        private boolean isThisOurStaticSource(RouteNode n,
                                      NetType type,
                                      boolean debug)
        Determines if the given node can serve as our sink and updates the net PIPs respectively if they can be used.
        Parameters:
        n - RouteNode in question
        type - The net type to designate the static source type
        Returns:
        true if this sources is useable and updates the netPIPs accordingly, false otherwise.

        public void routePinsReEntrant(java.util.ArrayList<Pin> pins,
                               boolean routeUnroutedNets)
        This is a specialized routing function that will only route the pins given. It is assumed that each pin provided already belongs to a net. If any PIPs have already been used on the net, they can be leveraged on this route.
        Parameters:
        pins - The sink pins to be routed.
